  "text": "where θ is the angle that the normal to ∂Ω makes with respect to the x-axis, evaluated at the point f −1 (e iϕ ). Finding the optimal director field has now been reduced to an iteration of the above equation, and when the sequence converges the director field can simply be found by first calculating Ξ through Eq. (24), and subsequently evaluating Θ = Ξ • f . Each iteration step in the above scheme requires only two Fourier transforms, which can be done both accurately and fast using Fast Fourier Transforms (FFTs) [CITATION_1] . Moreover, the above iteration scheme is easy to implement, making the determination of the optimal director field for a fixed shape with a known conformal map a simple computational task.",
